text: Prée-d'Anjou is a commune of 1,421 people (2017). It is found in the region Pays de la Loire in the Mayenne department in the northwest of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2018 and consists of the former communes of Laigné (the seat) and Ampoigné.Arrêté préfectoral 2 August 2017 == References == Category:2018 establishments in France Category:Communes in Mayenne
title: Prée-d'Anjou
